	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">caitsith2 wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Any progress on this FPGA SPC-700 project at all?</div>
<br />
<br />Yes and no.  Since I posted that, I made the hardware, debugged it, got a miniDOS running, and added SID, NSF (NES+N106+VRC6+MMC5+FME7), pokey, and FM (OPL3).  
<br />
<br />I got about 90% of the SPC-700 CPU done the weekend I asked for the info but then circuit boards and parts came so I was busy putting it together and all that.
<br />
<br />It's going to be a chiptune+MIDI synth in the end, but right now it's just a chiptune player.  At the moment it is playing SIDs, SAP, NSF, CMF, RAW, IMF, MUS, and some other formats.   SPC is still there ready to be finished but I've been working on getting everything else done first.
<br />
<br />It is reading those files right off of SD cards now (normal and SD-HC) using some 6502 code and the FPGA stuff.  
<br />
<br />You can keep track of progress on my blog, though I haven't posted in awhile.  I should update it with some mp3s and such but I've been working like hell on it and haven't done the blog updates.
<br />
<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://blog.kevtris.org/">http://blog.kevtris.org/</a><!-- m -->

		

